<p>
Swiss QR Code is a two-dimensional (2D) barcode type intended to encode and store payment and financial information in a graphical format. It is specifically designed for use in Switzerland and is based on the international ISO/IEC 18004 standard for QR Codes. Swiss QR Codes facilitate the exchange of payment and financial information between banks, businesses, and individuals. They can be scanned using smartphones or other devices equipped with an image sensor and can be used to initiate and complete financial transactions in a convenient and secure way. Swiss QR Codes have a variety of applications, including online and in-store payments, bill payments, and other financial transactions. This standard is aimed to simplify payment processes, improve accuracy, and promote interoperability between banks, businesses, and individuals across Switzerland.
</p>
